	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1"/>
				<p><add>German&#63;</add></p>
			<pb n="2"/>
				<p><add>Hebrew</add></p>
			<pb n="3"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Cleveland</placeName> <date>March 10<hi rend="sup">th</hi> 1856</date></p>
				<p>Dear Sir&#58;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">When I saw the first issue of the journal &#8222;Sinai<lb/> with headline &#8222;I am looking for my brothers&#8221;&#44; I thought of<lb/> a cunning answer&#44; namely &#8222;they have gone away from<lb/> here.  This impelled me to do the <sic>vers</sic> which I wrote on<lb/> the opposite page.&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">He asks to leave it printed in <persName>Lessers</persName> <add>&#63;</add> paper.<lb/>  If it is not printed there he will send it to the Israelite.<lb/>  He also intends to make an essay on the <add>&#63;</add> of <del>the</del><lb/> modern Jewism to the <sic>talmud</sic>.</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)">Signed</p>
			<p rend="indent(10)"><persName role="author">Joseph Levi</persName></p>
			<pb n="4"/>
				<p rend="align(center)"><hi rend="underline">Good Advice to Truth&#45;Lovers</hi></p>
				<p>Much noise from <placeName>Baltimore</placeName>&#44; new things recently came&#44;<lb/> A man called <persName>Einhorn</persName> invented them&#44; their like has never been<lb/> heard.<lb/>  Who is this man&#63;  What is his thought&#63;  <sic>people</sic> ask each other<lb/> But to me a thought comes stealthily&#44; though it is a<lb/> thought of  some importance&#44;<lb/> That this man is himself confused&#44; he lost his way.<lb/>  He goes about calling&#44; &#8220;My brethren I seek.&#8221;<lb/>  &#91;Beware&#33;&#44; lest he be to you a stumbling&#45;block&#93;<lb/>  Do this&#44; and live&#8212;say to him&#44; &#8220;They have moved<lb/> away from here&#42;&#8221;.</p>
			<p rend="indent(8)">&#40;signed&#41; Your brother <persName role="author">Joseph Halevi</persName></p>
				<p>&#42;He refers here in a footnote to the explanation by <persName>Rashi</persName><lb/> of <hi rend="underline">Genesis 37&#58;17</hi>.  About this verse <persName>Rashi</persName> says that<lb/> the angels meaning was &#8220;They have given up their<lb/> brotherliness.&#8221;</p>
		</body>
